}}'''José Celso Martinez Corrêa''', known as '''Zé Celso''' (born 30 March 1937), is a [[Brazil]]ian stage actor, director and playwright.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.br/books?id=iSrgDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA56&lpg=PA56&dq=z%C3%A9+celso+playwright&source=bl&ots=jxnVQdv3MG&sig=nhP2ZTl-ZRM6lBk79wSii1GMBGA&hl=pt-BR&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwik5MjBx8DWAhVhiVQKHQM8CS8Q6AEIZDAL#v=onepage&q=z%C3%A9%20celso%20playwright&f=false|title=The Modern Brazilian Stage|last=George|first=David|date=2011-03-30|publisher=University of Texas Press|isbn=9780292729766|language=en}}</ref> He was one of the founders of [[Teatro Oficina]], an innovative and politically active theater company associated with the 1960s [[Tropicalismo]] movement.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.br/books?id=JRXjAQAAQBAJ&pg=PP11&dq=jos%C3%A9+celso+martinez+correa+brazil&hl=pt-BR&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwja2v_WvcDWAhVGxlQKHSKYAZsQ6AEIXDAJ#v=onepage&q=jos%C3%A9%20celso%20martinez%20correa%20brazil&f=false|title=Brutality Garden: Tropicália and the Emergence of a Brazilian Counterculture|last=Dunn|first=Christopher|date=2014-01-01|publisher=UNC Press Books|isbn=9781469615707|language=en}}</ref>

Zé Celso became notable in the scene with his adaptation of [[Oswald de Andrade]]'s play'' O Rei da Vela'' (The Candle King), in 1967.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.br/books?id=NU1GAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA64&dq=jos%C3%A9+celso+martinez+correa+brazil&hl=pt-BR&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiqqprrxsDWAhUJsFQKHYsDCVMQ6AEISTAG#v=onepage&q=jos%C3%A9%20celso%20martinez%20correa%20brazil&f=false|title=World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre: The Americas|last=Rubin|first=Don|last2=Solorzano|first2=Carlos|date=2013-10-08|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781136359286|language=en}}</ref> He also co-wrote with [[Chico Buarque]] the 1968 play ''Roda Viva,'' who was targeted as ''pornographic'' and censored during the [[Brazilian military dictatorship|military dictatorship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br/porto-alegre/noticia/2016/03/o-dia-em-que-o-espetaculo-roda-viva-de-chico-buarque-foi-reprimido-em-porto-alegre-5292884.html|title=GaúchaZH|website=gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br|language=pt-BR|access-date=2017-09-25}}</ref>  One of his most recent plays is ''Os Sertões'', a trilogy adapting [[Os sertões|the book]] by [[Euclides da Cunha]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/os-sertoes-do-teatro-oficina-faz-mini-turne-pelo-brasil-4157264|title='Os Sertões', do Teatro Oficina, faz mini turnê pelo Brasil|date=2007-09-04|work=O Globo|access-date=2017-09-25|language=pt-BR}}</ref>

